      "message": "You don’t need a union at all as things stand now.\n\nIf Fuchsia has a plan to support 32-on-64 at some point, then you can leave the union alone, although since the #ifdefs are wrong for that, it doesn’t seem to be helping much. (You’d want ARCH_CPU_X86_FAMILY and ARCH_CPU_ARM_FAMILY to be prepared for that.) Linux is the model in this case.\n\nIf you get rid of the union surrounding these context fields, you’d leave the #ifdefs as they stand now, and rename the subfields to just be context_. We don’t currently have a model for this because every other OS we have does support 32-on-64.",
